  {"a":"xayah_bot","b":"ziggs","win":["Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Xayah","Xayah","Xayah"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"This is all Ziggs: his Bouncing Bomb (Q) outranges your autos and shoves the wave into your tower for free, so you're stuck last-hitting under turret while he pokes you with Q and zones you off melee minions with Satchel Charge (W) and Hexplosive Minefield (E). Farm safely at max range, accept the chip, and never walk up into a Q-into-E combo."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"You start to claw back at 6 because Featherstorm (R) gives you a threat he can't answer: the untargetable dash closes his poke gap and dodges his Satchel (W) knockback, and his global Mega Inferno Bomb (R) does nothing in a 2v2 skirmish. With a five-feather E root plus support CC you can finally punish his short-ranged escape."},{"when":"1st item","text":"The matchup flips to you at one item: Ziggs is a poke-only mage with no reliable self-peel once you're on top of him, so a completed crit component plus Clean Cuts blades means an R-engage into E-root deletes him. Look to all-in whenever his Satchel Charge is on cooldown — that's his only disengage."},{"when":"Late","text":"You outscale him hard: Ziggs stays a squishy artillery mage while your feather stacks and Featherstorm let you dive the backline untargetable. In fights, R past his minefield and W, blow up a five-feather E on him, and force him to burn Satchel on the escape so your team collapses."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive the poke phase then all-in at one item","R-engage and E-root him when Satchel (W) is down","Force him to burn Satchel Charge on escape"],"foe":["Poke and shove with Bouncing Bomb (Q) into your tower","Zone you off minions with Hexplosive Minefield (E)","Knock you away with Satchel Charge (W) to reset poke"]},"early":"Ziggs owns levels 1-4: his Q outranges you and perma-shoves, so you last-hit under tower eating poke while his W and E zone you off farm — play max range and take the chip.","mid":"At 6 Featherstorm gives you the gap-closer he can't answer, and his global R is useless in a 2v2, so with a feather-stacked E and support CC you start punishing him.","late":"You outscale from one item on: he's a self-peel-less poke mage, so R-engage past his minefield, blow up a five-feather E, and force his Satchel on the escape while your team collapses.","whys":["Ziggs's Bouncing Bomb outranges your autos and shoves you under tower at level 1.","At 2 his Q poke and minefield zone keep you off the wave with no answer.","Level 3 he adds Satchel knockback to reset poke and deny your last-hits.","Through 4-5 he perma-shoves and chips you while you farm defensively under turret.","At 6 Featherstorm closes his gap and his global ult is dead weight in the 2v2, flipping tempo to you.","At one item your R-engage into E-root beats a poke mage with no self-peel.","With two items your feather stacks and untargetable dive outscale his squishy artillery kit."]}
